d becomes clumpier as it rises\nupwards and expands away from the neutron star. Modelling the warped disk\nshape, we create a 2D map of wind properties. This unique measurement of the\nvertical structure of an accretion disk wind allows direct comparisons to 3D\nglobal simulations to reveal the outflow launching mechanism.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Apr 2023 20:45:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-13"}
